\begin_layout Plain Layout
Equation 1.3.
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left(A\cdot B\right)^{T}=B^{T}\cdot A^{T}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say we have 
\begin_inset Formula $A\in M_{m,n}\left(\mathbb{K}\right)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $B\in M_{n,p}\left(\mathbb{K}\right)$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\left(A\cdot B\right)^{T} & =\left(\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
A_{1,1} & \dots & A_{1,n}\\
\vdots & \ddots\\
A_{m,1} &  & A_{m,n}
\end{array}\right]\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
B_{1,1} & \dots & B_{1,p}\\
\vdots & \ddots\\
B_{n,1} &  & B_{n,p}
\end{array}\right]\right)^{T}\\
= & \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
\left(AB\right)_{1,1} & \left(AB\right)_{1,2} & \dots & \left(AB\right)_{1,p}\\
\vdots & \ddots\\
\left(AB\right)_{m,1} & \dots & \dots & \left(AB\right)_{m,p}
\end{array}\right]^{T}\\
= & \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
\left(AB\right)_{1,1} & \left(AB\right)_{2,1} & \dots & \left(AB\right)_{m,1}\\
\vdots & \ddots\\
\left(AB\right)_{1,p} & \dots & \dots & \left(AB\right)_{m,p}
\end{array}\right]\\
= & \left[\begin{array}{ccc}
B_{1,1} & \dots & B_{n,1}\\
\vdots & \ddots\\
B_{1,p} &  & B_{n,p}
\end{array}\right]\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
A_{1,1} & \dots & A_{m,1}\\
\vdots & \ddots\\
A_{1,n} &  & A_{m,n}
\end{array}\right]\\
= & B^{T}\cdot A^{T}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

Here we use the definion of (1.2) of product mulitplication here: 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(AB\right)_{ij}=$
\end_inset

 row i of 
\begin_inset Formula $A\cdot$
\end_inset

 column of 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

