\begin_layout Part*
Chapter 2 Exercises
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Before we start, let's do a recap 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
emoji{relieved-face}
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 is the motion in 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{C}$
\end_inset

;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
B is the same motion but in 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

, so 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho$
\end_inset

 is basically taking 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 to make such a 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 is the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

encoder
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 from 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{C}$
\end_inset

 to 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Ex.
 2.1.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Prove that definition of 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho_{n}$
\end_inset

 in the text makes diagram 2.1 commute.
 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


